SIMPLE: distortion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Distortion
<hw>Dis*tor"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>distortio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>distortion</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of distorting, or twisting out of natural or regular shape;
a twisting or writhing motion; <as>as, the <ex>distortions</ex> of the
face or body</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wresting from the true meaning.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Wren.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The state of being distorted, or twisted out of
shape or out of true position; crookedness; perversion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An unnatural deviation of shape or
position of any part of the body producing visible deformity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Distortive</ent>⟦br⟧
